Dear Us,

17 “He reached down from on high and took hold of me;  he drew me out of deep waters.

24 I have been blameless before him  and have kept myself from sin.

29 You, Lord, are my lamp;  the Lord turns my darkness into light.

What are you grateful for? 

Dear Us, 
I’ve had highs and I’ve had lows… I am just a kid from North Philly with a grateful soul… 

With highs and lows… I have learned you must be grateful for both of them. They’ve helped me to thank GOD more and depend more on GOD. If you have highs and lows just have a grateful heart it will help your soul. 

If you are out there, know you matter. Your story matters… who you are on this planet matters. Also, I am grateful for you… “I have not stopped giving thanks for you, remembering you in my prayers.” Ephesians 1:16

NOTE: Gratitude is the seed for GOD to do more in your Life. 

EXERCISE: When you wake up and before you go to sleep. 
1. Sit or lay on the floor 
2. Say or Write Down 10 things you’re Grateful for. 
3. BONUS: Ask people what their grateful for. 

REMEMBER: Be grateful for what you have in pursuit of what you want. 
Much Love, Joy and Respect, 
Miguel

ART with no easel 

Dear Us, 
The things you have went thru has made you who you are but also your thoughts for a brighter future… have contributed in such a beautiful way. 

Now as you live in the moment with a GODLY imagination for a greater future. You have the advantage! It’s safe to say it’s “Best of both world” 

In the mean time between time: 
• Make today count. 
• Count your blessings and make them count 
• Appreciate everything and everyone in your life.
•Share more of yourself with the world. 
• Be more authentic.
• Love more. Care more. Listen more. Be more compassionate.
• Lighten the whole world with your smile and great attitude.
• Above all live to make GOD proud
• Be brave. Be courageous.
• Test your limits. Do the impossible.
• Focus on the process.
• Become better every day.
• Try harder. Go the extra mile.

Remember: Water & Nurture great thoughts, for you will never go higher than your thoughts.

“But as for you(___your name___), be strong and do not give up, for your work will be rewarded.”
‭‭2 Chronicles‬ ‭15‬:‭7‬ ‭

Much Love, Joy and Respect,
Miguel
